{"_id":"0X7PKRvUOzBlMUPp","name":"Blood Tells","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>A flagellant, you regularly beat yourself to awaken your lost god. If you inflict d3 HP of damage to yourself prior to combat, you gain +2 to a number of rolls equal to the HP lost.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"IDPP79h9ZRC0teUV","name":"False Gods","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>You are literate and can use scrolls, but must pass a DR12 Presence test when encountering them not to immediately attempt to destroy them as words of false gods. If you start with a scroll, consider that you passed the test.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"LcrrblaQhmTgi5Rw","name":"Smell of Decay","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Not only is your god dead, but their odour of decay pervades you. Tests to defend against attacks have a +2 bonus due to the gut-wrenching stench</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"Q0jvO79qsFt5IWDY","name":"Dead Gods Prophet","type":"class","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"abilities":"<p>Wise, roll 3D6+2 for Presence. Weak, roll 3D6&minus;2 for Strength. Ordinary starting equipment plus one random scroll (sacred or unclean). Roll a D4 on the weapons table and D2 on the armor table. You also begin with one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Master of Fate</li>\n<li>Book of Boiling Blood</li>\n<li>Speaker of Truths</li>\n<li>Initiate of the Invisible College</li>\n<li>Bard of the Undying</li>\n<li>Hawk as Weapon</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Eldritch Origins, d6</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Awakening, adult, in a ritual circle underneath the northern bridge to Grift.</li>\n<li>Wandered, memoryless, from the mouth of a cavern at the cliffs of Terion.</li>\n<li>Single child survivor of an incident in the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead.</li>\n<li>Dying of plague in a Bergen Chrypt hovel, you touched something from outside.</li>\n<li>An average individual until you encountered something in a dim glade in Sarkash.</li>\n<li>Raised on a lonely island in Lake Onda. No one else has ever heard of this island and you can&rsquo;t return.</li>\n</ol>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"You hear voices in your head, telling you what to do. Or at least you think you do. You are the prophet of a god; only your god is dead, slain by the Basilisk SHE within the wretched peaks of the Bergen Chrypt. Now no one wants to hear the words of your god. But you can still hear them. Day and night. Like hot wires through your brain.","omenDie":"1d3","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d4","startingItems":"frontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,False Gods","startingPresence":"3d6+2","startingRolls":"frontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,Gift One,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,Gift Two,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,Name Your God Subtable 1,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,Name Your God Subtable 2,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-dead-gods-prophet,Name Your God Subtable 3,1","startingSilver":"1d6*5","startingStrength":"3d6","startingToughness":"3d6-2","weaponTableDie":"1d4"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.ifSBk6ORiHgq3Xhr"}}}
{"_id":"W7ag6nMbTLm0qvwb","name":"In Death I Live","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>When you die, make a DR14 Presence test. If you pass, your god refuses you into the afterlife and you recover with 1HP. If you fail, your body is consumed in holy flames.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"Yd8Qgntlsx9IGAsx","name":"Incoherent Sophistic Babble","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Concentrate to babble an ungodly litany. So disconcerting is this chant that those who hear it must pass a DR10 Presence test or lose their next action</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"fAiKQ6qIyTwwI8Wn","name":"Eyes of Holy Fire","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Your pupils burn with the soul of your lord. Once per combat you may make an attack (DR10), as fire spurts from your eyes, d6 damage. You are left blinded for the rest of the fight.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"fvsiJmMEBRs9TwUA","name":"Ichor of Rot","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>The foul fluids of your god&rsquo;s rot run from your hands-a black stigmata. As an DR12 attack you can wipe your hands on the bare skin of your assailants, who must then pass a DR12 Toughness test or descend into frothing spasms for two turns.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"nzVQbFrGSaW5qSOA","name":"Lord of Nothing","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>You wear a bizarre arrangement of garments and scraps that make you look like the parody of a king or queen. Still, you gain +2 to rolls to impress the easily fooled.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
{"_id":"xzyMtVEo8Ie1bFCV","name":"My Body, A Vessel","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/dead-gods-prophet.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Your god may be dead, but what is death to a god? Once a day you may allow the ghost of you god to enter your flesh and reveal a truth. Ask the GM one yes/no question that they must answer truthfully. The god then departs, leaving you weakened and frail.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.aOqgJ2VdoDHSswBt"}}}
